    "faq_YGRTq6": {
      "type": "faq",
      "blocks": {
        "question_MELLWg": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "question": "What is a Promise Ring?",
            "answer": "<p>A promise ring symbolises commitment and intention between two people. It often represents loyalty, love or a future engagement.</p>"
          }
        },
        "question_Xxy4jk": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "question": " Which finger do you wear a promise ring on?",
            "answer": "<p>Promise rings are commonly worn on the ring finger of the left or right hand, depending on personal preference but the beauty of The Promise Co. is that our Promise rings are designed for your story. Whether that be a Pinky Promise ring or a traditional placement!</p>"
          }
        },
        "question_FxKcTH": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Are promise rings the same as engagement rings?",
            "answer": "<p>The short answer, <strong>no.</strong></p><p>Promise rings can be given for a variety of reasons:</p><p><strong>Loyalty in Relationships: </strong>A Promise ring is a brilliant way to show your commitment and seriousness in a relationship, a way to show your partner your love and that your Promise to stay together through thick & thin!</p><p><strong>A celebration of a milestone</strong>: Whether in a relationship or gifting to a loved friend or family member, a birthday, anniversary or milestone event (like graduating!) are great times to buy someone a Promise Ring. It will serve as a little reminder of such a special time and give you the opportunity to make a Promise. </p><p><strong>Long Distance: </strong>Long distance can be tricky, but having something to look at everyday to \"feel\" your partners presence can certainly help. A Promise Ring is a way to feel constantly connected to your partner no matter the miles between you.</p><p><strong>A promise of future engagement or marriage:</strong> you may not be able to get married due to age, finance or geographical location. You may not even want a wedding... but like the idea of that next step in commitment and want something on your ring finger to say to the world you are in a loving relationship! A Promise Ring is your way of showing commitment without the wedding.</p><p><strong>Acknowledging a Significant Change:</strong> Given during times of significant change, like job transitions, relocations, or other life-altering events... We have seen people buy Promise Rings for their partners as \"Push Presents\" as a Promise to be a great dad (Super cute)</p><p>We like to think of a Promise Ring as your own \"Wearable Story\", it can be a Promise or a reminder of anything that is meaningful to you!</p>"
          }
        },
        "question_hKtdMz": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Can promise rings be worn every day?",
            "answer": "<p>Yes. Our rings are designed for daily wear with durable materials and comfortable settings. We use the best plating and anti tarnish coating. With x25 thicker 18ct Gold Vermeil and Rhodium plated Sterling Silver. We offer the best quality for the most affordable price.</p>"
          }
        },
        "question_X4dChg": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Is a Purity Ring the same as a Promise Ring?",
            "answer": "<p>A promise ring and a purity ring are sometimes confused, but they don’t mean the same thing. A purity ring is traditionally linked to a personal or religious commitment, often connected to abstinence before marriage.</p><p>A promise ring, however, has a much broader meaning. It can symbolise a promise between partners, friends, or even a promise to yourself. Today, promise rings are most often worn as a reminder of love, commitment, personal growth, or an important moment in someone’s life.</p>"
          }
        }
      },
